==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stringent
<hw>Strin"gent</hw> <pr>(str⟦icr⟧n"j⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>stringens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>stringere</ets> to draw or bind tight. See <er>Strain</er>.]</ety>
<def>Binding strongly; making strict requirements; restrictive; rigid;
severe; <as>as, <ex>stringent</ex> rules</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They must be subject to a sharper penal code, and to a more
<qex>stringent</qex> code of procedure.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Strin"gent*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Strin"gent*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stringer</ent>⟦br⟧
